67.6	Ignatius_of_Loyola	Ignatius of Loyola	Ignatius of Loyola (Basque: , Spanish: ) (1491 â€“ July 31, 1556) was a Spanish knight from a Basque noble family, hermit, priest since 1537, and theologian, who founded the Society of Jesus (Jesuits) and was its first Superior General. Ignatius emerged as a religious leader during the Counter-Reformation. Loyola's devotion to the Catholic Church was characterized by unquestioning obedience to the Catholic Church's authority and hierarchy.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/15/St_Ignatius_of_Loyola_%281491-1556%29_Founder_of_the_Jesuits.jpg/180px-St_Ignatius_of_Loyola_%281491-1556%29_Founder_of_the_Jesuits.jpg
